obile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529314\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kpe1665702920480.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kpe1665702920480.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kpe1665702920480.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kpe1665702920480\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Handling Data Validation Errors\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When the validation process fails, ProcScript functions provide information about the failure.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__p_d45203e1_d45204e1_d45205e1\">When an error occurs:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__li_d22454e1_d22455e1_d22456e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"udd1665702579942.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/udd1665702579942.html\" title=\"Determines whether the status data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. This attribute holds the occurrence modification state. It can be set or inspected using $occstatus. Valid values are True or False (default).\">Status</a> contains a negative value\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__li_d22457e1_d22458e1_d22459e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ypd1665702576258.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ypd1665702576258.html\" title=\"Return the reason for an error in ProcScript execution.\">$procerror</a> gives the detailed reason\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__li_d22460e1_d22461e1_d22462e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"opq1665702649630.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/opq1665702649630.html\" title=\"Return the location of the error specified by $procerror.\">$procerrorcontext</a> identifies exactly where the error occurred in ProcScript\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__li_d22463e1_d22464e1_d22465e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jqe1665702576424.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jqe1665702576424.html\" title=\"Return the context of the last validation error.\">$dataerrorcontext</a> identifies the data context where the error occurred\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__p_d45206e1_d45207e1_d45208e1\">If declarative or procedural validation fails, Uniface activates the field-level or entity-level error trigger as appropriate for each occurrence, and sets <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$error</span> to the relevant value to indicate why the validation process has failed. <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$error</span> is set to:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__li_d22466e1_d22467e1_d22468e1\">0140 for the field-level validate trigger\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__li_d22469e1_d22470e1_d22471e1\">0147 for the validateKey or entity-level validate trigger\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__p_d45209e1_d45210e1_d45211e1\">After validation is completed, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$dataerrorcontext</span> are set to reflect the first validation error encountered by the validate statement. These functions therefore provide different values during the validation process:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__li_d22472e1_d22473e1_d22474e1\">During the validation process, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$dataerrorcontext</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerrorcontext</span> return values for the current validation error.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__li_d22475e1_d22476e1_d22477e1\">After validation is completed, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$dataerrorcontext</span> return values for the first error encountered in the validation process.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpe1665702920480__p_d45212e1_d45213e1_d45214e1\">For example, when validation of an occurrence is requested, Uniface first attempts to validate the first field of the primary key. If validation fails for the first field of the primary key, Uniface activates the error trigger for that field.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529314\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529314\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Handling Data Validation Errors Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Handling Data Validation Errors When the validation process fails, ProcScript functions provide information about the failure. When an error occurs: Status contains a negative value $procerror gives the detailed reason $procerrorcontext identifies exactly where the error occurred in ProcScript $dataerrorcontext identifies the data context where the error occurred If declarative or procedural validation fails, Uniface activates the field-level or entity-level error trigger as appropriate for each occurrence, and sets $error to the relevant value to indicate why the validation process has failed. $error is set to: 0140 for the field-level validate trigger 0147 for the validateKey or entity-level validate trigger After validation is completed, $status , $procerror , and $dataerrorcontext are set to reflect the first validation error encountered by the validate statement. These functions therefore provide different values during the validation process: During the validation process, $status , $procerror , $dataerrorcontext , and $procerrorcontext return values for the current validation error. After validation is completed, $status , $procerror and $dataerrorcontext return values for the first error encountered in the validation process. For example, when validation of an occurrence is requested, Uniface first attempts to validate the first field of the primary key. If validation fails for the first field of the primary key, Uniface activates the error trigger for that field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}